<p>How do I apply a class to an SVG text element using a group?</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1"   font-family="arial" font-size="12pt" width="600"&gt;    &lt;style&gt;   text.ginormous  { font-size:48pt } &lt;/style&gt;  &lt;g style="class:ginormous"&gt;    &lt;text x="50" y="50" &gt;no dice&lt;/text&gt; &lt;/g&gt;    &lt;text class="ginormous" x="50" y="120" &gt;this works&lt;/text&gt;   &lt;/svg&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>